fields.description:
Currently our workflows include "Cleanup" step goal of which is to remove Docker image built during the workflow, but since GitHub is using dynamicly created runners, their environment is discarded after job is completed, and such, that cleanup is performed for us.
Goal of this ticket is to remove cleanup step from our workflows:

{code:java}
      # This step cleans up the docker image from the system.
      - name: Cleanup
        #if: always()
        if: ${{ inputs.perform_deploy || github.event_name != 'workflow_dispatch' }}
        run: |
          echo "Docker Images before cleanup"
          docker image ls
          echo "Clean repository images"
          if docker images --format '${{ env.ECR_REPO_NAME }}:${{ env.ARTIFACT_NAME }}' | grep -q '${{ env.ARTIFACT_NAME }}'; then
            docker rmi $(docker images --format '${{ env.ECR_REPO_NAME }}:${{ env.ARTIFACT_NAME }}' | grep '${{ env.ARTIFACT_NAME }}') -f
          else
            echo "No repo image found."
          fi
          echo "Docker Prune"
          docker system prune -f
          echo "Docker Images after cleanup"
          docker image ls    
{code}
fields.summary: Remove unnecessary docker cleanup step

HI there,

We received a notice today that Apple now accepts subtitles for shortform:[https://help.apple.com/itc/videoaudioassetguide/#/itc14cfe734c]

It probably makes sense to include ITT for Short form after all?



here are the bullets from the link above so they are handy:
 * Delivered in an iTunes Timed Text (iTT) formatted file, using{{.itt}}file extension.

 * Delivered in the same package with the video it references as an asset in the{{<assets>}}block.

 * Only one{{div}}element is allowed in an ITT document.

 * {{timeBase}}must be set to{{{}smpte{}}}.

 * {{dropMode}}must be set to{{"dropNTSC"}}or{{{}"nonDrop"{}}}; iTunes Timed Text does not support{{{}dropPAL{}}}.

 * Only{{sansSerif}}may be specified as the typeface in{{{}fontFamily{}}}.

issues: Temp Audio Master Flag in AOMA

fields.description:
We are getting more questions about the recent update to the Master KPI in relation to the details of the AOMA publish status being used.
 
G010005465687R where the AOMA status says:  Cannot publish: Response from AOMA webservice: Product G010005465687R is not publish ready: 'I Look Good' (Digital Audio Track) product is not ready for publish; No cover master; Audio Master WAV 24 Bit 26468075 has locked QC notes; Audio Master WAV 16 Bit 26468076 has locked QC notes; All tracks of the product are linked to track masters; All linked audio tracks have at least one linked master with assets
 
Workability is showing:  Cover = Red X and Master = Red X
The expectation would be: Cover = Red X and Master = Green check
 
Is the KPI literally reading the "not publish ready" and saying there is no master. If yes why is that - is it because of the "locked QC notes" not allowing the master file that is there to be recognized?
 
Unfortunately, I think we are finding too many instances that are contradicting what users were expecting to see in the Workability dashboard for Masters. We might need to revisit the logic.

Ziggy Pothoff confirmed: yes, this is exactly what is happening: the aoma web service is saying the product is neither open nor full publish ready and consequently the master KPI says "No", because even though there is a master file registered it's not "ready for use". I'd like to do a little more investigation with the asset service that AOMA provides to us, to make sure we can get all the information we need from it, and do not require an update on their side.  Also, going down to the track level like this may impact performance, especially on products with many tracks, so we need to make sure we don't end up slowing the dashboard down. So let's do a little more analysis and regroup.
fields.summary: Master KPI Logic
